<h2 id="beta">2. BETA SOFTWARE; NATURE OF THE SERVICES</h2>
<p>
  The App connects you with other users for time-limited, one-to-one conversations on topics where you may hold different views, using a username, state, and personalized icon to represent you rather than your full identity. Conversations are moderated by an AI system, and Dialog Lab staff may review conversation content as described in Section 12. See our <a href="/privacypolicy/">Privacy Policy</a> for more detail on what information is shared with a conversation partner and how conversation data is used.
</p>
<p>
  The App is currently offered as a pre-release, beta version (the "Beta Services"). The Beta Services are under active development and may contain bugs, errors, and other defects; may be modified, suspended, or discontinued at any time without notice; and may not operate reliably or as intended. Use of the Beta Services may result in unexpected results, data loss, or downtime. You are solely responsible for backing up any data used in connection with the Beta Services.
</p>
<p>
  We are under no obligation to provide any support, maintenance, updates, or bug fixes for the Beta Services, and we make no commitment regarding uptime, availability, or response times during the beta period.
</p>
<p>
  The Beta Services, and any non-public features, functionality, performance information, or roadmap information you learn about through your participation (collectively, "Beta Information"), are provided to you in confidence. We ask that you use reasonable discretion regarding public discussion of Beta Information — including social media posts, reviews, screenshots, and recordings — prior to our public release or announcement of the applicable feature.
</p>

